                <h3>Nevada tourist attractions cities-</h3>
                <h4 class="text-justify">1. Reno </h4>
                <p class="text-justify">The signboard of Reno reads“the biggest little city in the world. “In terms of population, Reno is the second-largest city in Nevada after Las Vegas. It is still relatively small and home to only approximately 250,000 residents. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">Reno is the hub of many championships like the annual National Championship Air Races, The Great Reno Balloon Race, and the Hot August Nights car convention. Reno is also the host of the National Automobile Museum. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">It also offers an excellent mix of gaming, cultural, outdoor, and fun attractions for all ages. It also has the largest ski facilities within just 50 miles of the city. The West Street Market, open seven days a week, is the dreamland for foodies, offering all kinds and cultures of food. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">2. Carson City</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">Aside from being the capital of Nevada, it offers visitors a good selection of historical, cultural, and outdoor attractions to suit all tastes. History enthusiasts can visit the Nevada State Capitol Building, the Nevada State Museum, and Nevada State Railroad Museum. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">Art lovers will enjoy the galleries and performing arts places at the Brewery Arts Center. There are many art galleries downtown. Tourists can also enjoy hiking and biking along several trails or shopping along Curry Street. This city also offers a pleasant ride to Virginia City on the V & T Railway. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">3. Henderson</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">The city of Henderson also looms with the scent of history and culture. This city also hosts the imposing Hoover Dam and lovely Lake Mead. The historic buildings here provide information on the evolution of architecture and the development of the socio-economic condition of Nevada and the US. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">The children will love the Discovery Children’s Museum and the Ethel M. Chocolate Factory. This city also offers opportunities for Outdoor enthusiasts. It has excellent camping, picnicking, hiking, and rock climbing facilities at the Valley of Fire State Park. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">4. Boulder City</h4>
