                <p class="text-justify">For tourists with nerves of steel, a terrifying zip-line adventure with Flightlinez Bootleg Canyon awaits in Boulder City. They can also try Las Vegas gilder rides or the safe historic rail excursion from the Nevada Southern Railway Museum. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">5. Ruby Mountains</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">The Ruby Mountains are a range of magnificent mountains. Located in Northern Nevada, its content spreads 129km. visiting the Ruby Mountains demands a fair degree of dedication as the population there is less. The amount of paved roads is minimal. At the heart of the mountains is the u-shaped Lamoille Canyon. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">The Ruby Mountains have many places suitable for horseback riding. It also offers camping and hiking. Tourists can enjoy the local wildlife while hiking. 4-Wheeling and snowmobiling outside the wilderness area are also pretty standard. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">6. Tonopah</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">Tonopah is a place that will make the tourist want to break their journey and rewound in time in Nevada’s Silver Trails Territory. The Tonopah Historic Mining Park allows the tourists to see restored and reconstructed mining equipment, join an underground tour, watch a video, or take a self-guided walking tour. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">At the Central Nevada Museum, the tourists can feast their eyes on the town’s history. Tonopah is one of America’s best Stargazing destinations. Tourists can visit a local brewery and stargaze while sipping on their cup of wine. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">7. Rhyolite Ghost Town</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">The Rhyolite Ghost Town is 56km from the Furnace Creek Visitor’s Center, just outside the Death Valley National Park in Nevada. The town was once quite fancy, thanks to its gold mine back in 1904. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">In 2022, the tourists can stroll around the town's surviving buildings to get an idea of how the early miners and their families lived – the city boasted a three-story bank building, a stock exchange, two large schools, and an opera house, and two railway depots.For a brief six to seven years (until the mine was depleted), the town thrived solely on its fanciness, attracting flocks of investors. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">8. Area 51</h4>
                <p class="text-justify">Area 51 has always been cloaked in secrecy, attracting curiosity stronger than an electromagnet. To the best of public knowledge, it is a famous United States Air Force facility near Groom Lake in the southern Nevada Desert. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">A drive along the famous Extraterrestrial Highway, a portion of State Route 375, will be enough to fan the flames of UFO and alien enthusiasts. It features some amusing “alien-related” road signs. To catch a glimpse of the top-secret facility, protected by restricted special-use airspace, visitors need to hike to the top of Tikaboo Peak, 42km from Area 51, which is the closest legal viewpoint. </p>

                <h4 class="text-justify">9. Sparks</h4>
